Meet <b>David</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>David lives at <a href='/home/?user=ronster18'>27470 Twilight Lane</a>, in one of the more rural areas of Millsberry:  beautiful Golden Valley.  He has been a citizen here since February 3rd of 2005, and is quite happy with his new home. <br><br>David is also very happy about attending Millsberry Academy.  His new classmates describe him as being a little shy, but really funny once you've gotten to know him.  His teammates on the Millsberry Academy basketball team are happy to have him, since he's very quick and gives a total effort every time he's on the court.  His great personality and willingness to selflessly dive after loose balls (sometimes even jumping into the stands!) have quickly made him popular with both teammates and fans alike.<br><br>Aside from his interest in sports, David also enjoys listening to music.  His favorite types are rap, rhythm & blues, plus drum 'n' bass.  He'll often play music on his stereo when his friends are over and they're playing games.  Whether it be computer, video, or board games, David loves them all!<br><br>On weekends, David and his friends often walk around the mall.  This weekend, he and his friends were rather excited about spotting Kelly Kimbell, the champion snowboarder who recently moved into town.  Kelly was wearing a really cool red jacket, which happens to be one of David's favorite colors (along with dark blue and green), and he complimented her on it.<br><br>After hanging out at the mall, David and his friends usually stop by Regio's Famous Pizza Parlor for dinner, where they laugh and joke, having a good time for hours.  Afterwards, they will head over to the Downtown Entertainment Complex and catch a late movie. <br><br>Congratulations on being a fine citizen, David. You truly deserve to be citizen of the week!</div>
